content: The daily readings app has made it very convenient to access the daily orthodox readings but the app isnt loading right now. It's been like that for months now and I'm getting drained. I looked forward to accessing it through the app everyday. I know I can access it somewhere else but there was something about it, having it on my phone, that made me want to read the scriptures more frequently.
Great

Absolutely love this app. It had helped me tremendously in my prayer life and thus my spiritual journey. BUT... It has not worked since yesterday. When I click the app it just shows the opening screen trying to load. I have a One Plus 7T phone. I rebooted the phone and also uninstalled and reinstalled the app. It still will not load üòî. Please HELP! God bless all involved in the creation and upkeep of this app üôè

Super thankful for the app! The ability to switch between light/dark/automatic display modes would be great. The old widget was pretty bad design-wise, but I would love to have a new minimalist one. Even better if you could choose what you'd like displayed on the widget [fasting, daily readings (choice for text or a button to open the reading in-app), feasts of the day, and even a prayer for the time of day].
Excellent App! VERY well worth the space on your device(s).

userName: Common Sense isn't 2 dimes and a nickel
content: I love this app. It helps me with my daily readings and prayers.
Decent App. Dark mode would be appreciated, low bandwidth locations cause the app to load very slowly and sometimes crash, cannot change to old calendar for times when traveling abroad or whatever.

App got slow to the point it wouldn't open at all, had to reinstall, now its fast again. Love that I can get my Daily Reading in wherever my downtime hapens and know if its a fasting day in a glance! No more falling into bed & thinking "Maybe tomorrow..." Thank you!!
Absolutely a wonderful App. I'm reading it daily, Very useful and resourceful. Through this App, I have become a very confident person when it comes to the Lord,
Great app for a Christian interested in keeping up with the reading of the Holy Scripture. Also getting to know about the lives of Saints is very useful.
Suddenly i can not retrieve any data. App only show blank page. Please check it.
Only thing I'd add is if there was a way to organise the prayers in it. But also to have it accept my own timezone.

buggy on both my Samsung Galaxy and now the new Google pixel. The widget, which I love, hasn't worked for ages unto ages, amen. wish info was provide about all of the listed saints, not just one or two. The content that is there is good. I appreciate this app and use it daily, which makes the bugginess all the more frustrating. Good practice for working on my salvation, right? üòâ

Great way to keep on top of daily readings! I have some requests though: PLEASE add dark mode support! The Windows Phone version had it and I miss it. It's also difficult to use in a low bandwidth setting. It can take almost a minute to start sometimes due to data usage. It would be great to reduce the amount transferred, and to support caching the next day overnight for offline use. Sometimes it even seems to reload just hitting the back button from a reading to main screen. Thank you!
Great and useful
Great app

This app is essential to my daily life. It's simple and easy to understand. Just open it up and everything that I need pops up. Thank you for developing this app and for making it free. ‚ò¶Ô∏è‚ò¶Ô∏è‚ò¶Ô∏è

Nice app, but after a while I noticed there is hardly any Old Testament or Psalms... but on a positive note, lots of New Testament and Gospels .... I felt like I needed more Psalms and Old Testament as well, for a more rounded daily scripture reading. App works well. follows the Orthodox Church Calendar.

I loved this app because I was able to have the widget on my screen. I could see if I was allowed to eat meat or not, without opening the program. I have no idea why they would deactivate the widget. It's a shame and now I regret paying for this app. It was a waist of my money. I hope that they will reinstall the widget again within a few days.
as a reletivly recent convert: this tool is simply a must have....i especially frequent the dedicated prayers section...it helps a great deal
really awesome and a great help

Great and handy app, however would request the following items: - Being able to swipe left and right between the epistle and gospel as you can on iOS. -provide additional prayers for before communion section, it appears this had quite a few however now as one or two. Other than that, please keep the blessed work up and thank you!

The widget was working on my Galaxy S6 but not on this fancypants S10+ I just got. Hopefully this will be fixed soon because I rely on it for daily and upcoming fasting and readings, especially during Great Lent! The app itself has been steadily improving and it is a daily help, thank you for providing it.
Doesn't work on my Samsung Galaxy Tab E or Samsung Galaxy S7. I'm very disappointed!
Couldn't get the app to open on my phone! It worked great until the last "update"! I had to delete the app! No need to keep it if it doesn't work!
never works
loaded up properly once, and every time after, it refuses to launch. waste of a dollar.
Its great but failing to load up today. I've restarted my phone and it's still bugged.
whoa. this is EXACTLY what i was hoping to find as new to the Orthodox Church

I love it, just one suggestion, where you can change the titles and contents to greek, its not all greek unfortunately. When i go to see the glossary its all English, and the prayers at the bottom are also in English. Otherwise amazing app!
Fantastic app
Excellent content, functionality and appearance. Would be nice to see the full text of the Hours and maybe notifications for them, though ‚ò∫
Nice way keep abreast of Saints and readings. Would like more extensive readings, and a better version of the Scriptures than the really weak RSV.
Already sent feedback

The calendar lacks information on the lives of saints. If it lists five, it 
provides information on one. For the other four, users get the exact same 
blurb on name days. I end up using the Russian calendar, which has 
extensive information on many saints, and jumping forward 13 days.
I was hoping that after 3 years you would have fixed the app... But it still crashes when I try to open the readings.

A very good tool for participating in the daily life of The Church, and enriching to those inquiring of or seeking Orthodoxy. I love the Online Chapel, but not having to go through several web pages makes life easier. God bless you!
Incredible app, everything you need. Way better than the lite edition.
Works very well!
Love it
I like most of the features, but I would like to see daily Old Testament readings as well, not just the New Testament.
Great daily insight into the life of The Church, saints and bible readings
I use this app daily. It is an  excellent app. I hope there will be a a section ion to add additional prayers like in the iOS app.

I like this but cannot give it five stars. I have an Note 4 as my personal phone and an iPhone as my work phone, and the trouble is that I paid for the premium version here on Android, yet it is missing features that I have on the free version of iPhone (Which is odd, it's usually the other way around.).  I like the app, however on the Apple version it prompts you with your prayer reminders throughout the day as well.  Very handy for those trying to keep a prayerful lifestyle. Outside of  that I think the app is great, and I certainly wouldn't switch to an iPhone because of it, they are too far behind in technology. Especially when compared to a Note.  If you could change that then I would be happy to give you a full five stars.
Great resource for fasting days and Holy days and Saints commemorated on this days.

Very useful in my spiritual life. Can you make an app for chanters like the Antiochian one which has the typicon and verses for the antiphons. Or maybe co-operate with their archdiocese of beruit to make it in Greek and English would be great

Is there a way to get the prayers in Arabic? And also in the prayer "The Jesus Prayer" there's a typo in the citation of Luke. It has 18:33 but the verse bring referenced is actually 18:13. (also I'm assuming that the glossary is still being updated, as I cannot click on any terms after "Litourgikon"?)... Great application and very edifying. God bless you very much.
Use it daily and is an integral part of prayer rule.
It makes things easier than going to your website
Best prayer guide and calendar for English language
Love the app! Could you add a verse of the day widget??
I can read the Bible passages and Saint bios, but can't access the prayers, glossary,  or search function.  :(
Works great on my LG phone and Samsung tablet. Easy to use and great to have.
Excellent, but you really do need to have all the saints.
I love this app, just need to make it easy to share things on social networks.
Overall, I like the app however it would be better if all the saints of the day had info on them not just some of them. I also have problems with it crashing.

This app has helped me greatly in doing daily readings as well as stay on top of fast and feast days.  It is easy to use and to look at.  I do wish it would be easier navigating from day to day.  They also do not information available for every saint yet.  It is well on its way to being an app essential for any orthodox christian.
So glad that you added Arabic!
This app is the most awesome app ever. I highly recomend..
I use with Pray Always! and AFR apps. Very much worn the money.  I use it on ASUS tablet TFT-101.
This is a great app. I use it all the time. The Developers continually make it better and they are very responsive.
Please add the prayer section that is available on IOS
Highly recommend it.  Overall a great app!
I just purchased the app and each time I try to open it, it crashes. Works great on my Kindle but not on my android phone.
Had this app on my iPhone 5 and loved it. Purchased it for my Samsung Galaxy Note II and can't find the prayer section that was available on the iPhone version. This is the only disappointment.
Very useful app. Contains daily Bible readings, 'apostle' readings, saints days etc.
Unable to download readings. There is nothing wrong with my Samsung Galaxy S2 android.
A very well put together app... Very helpful and well organized
This strengthens my interest in the Greek Orthodox Faith!!

This makes it so easy to read the Holy Scriptures for each day of the year, and you can look up other days, find a Saint. The language can be changed to Greek if you need to. All the Fathers of the Church say we NEED to read the Holy Scriptures daily. This is a first step requirement.
Pray unceasingly for Christ's forgiveness.
Excellent for finding daily readings and saints easily!
It would be even better if you had a widget so that I could see the saints every time I turn my phone on
A great app that keeps improving! How wonderful to have the daily readings and Saints at one's fingertips. Essential for all Orthodox Christians.
Excellent to see time and resources going into improving this app. It works flawlessly for me on my phone and tablet.
If you are Greek Orthodox, this is one of your most important apps.  Theo Karantsalis
This app is indispensable for Orthodox Christians who are devoted to reading Scripture and learning about the Saints. I use this everyday as part of my morning discipline of Worship.
Good brief daily  devotional app
I would give this app 6 stars.   I emailed the developer about making the app landscape and they were quick to email me back and then update the app.   Great app!
A must for every Orthodox
